# Copy to config.env (gitignored) to OVERRIDE the defaults. `make screenshots`
# sources it. For the standard Vagrant path you don't need this file at all — the
# Makefile already defaults every value below to the throwaway-VM dev credentials.
# Only set a key here when pointing at a non-default / existing instance.
#
# Targets. Leave these UNSET for the Vagrant path: seed/capture auto-resolve the
# VM's private (libvirt) IP and hit it directly. (We can't use localhost — the VM
# forwards 8080/3000 to the host, and if you also run sysmanage on the host those
# ports collide so localhost answers from the wrong instance.) Set them only to
# point at an existing instance — seed + capture are environment-agnostic.
# SCREENSHOT_TARGET_API=http://my-dev-box:8080    # backend (seed.py, fixture_agent.py)
# SCREENSHOT_TARGET_WEB=http://my-dev-box:3000    # web UI (capture.mjs)

# Admin account used to seed (matches the VM's sysmanage.yaml security.admin_userid
# and the password provision.sh sets). Defaulted in the Makefile; uncomment to override.
SCREENSHOT_ADMIN=admin@sysmanage.org
SCREENSHOT_ADMIN_PW=ChangeMe-Dev-Only!

# Account used to log the browser in for capture. Default: a seeded demo user.
SCREENSHOT_USER=alice.admin@demo.sysmanage.org
SCREENSHOT_PW=Demo-Pass-1!

# --- Pass two (tiers) — not used yet -----------------------------------------
# Path to a Professional+ license key file (NEVER commit this). When pass-two
# adds tier-specific screenshots, the pipeline will inject this, restart the
# backend, and capture the Pro/Enterprise/SaaS shots.
# SYSMANAGE_LICENSE_FILE=
